\section{Our Experiences}
\label{sec: ourexperiences}

In order to understand the perspectives of faculty, along with hearing and Deaf/HoH students, we asked each group to fill out an anonymous web based survey based upon their experiences. In the following sections, we discuss and analyze the feedback we received. To receive a well rounded set of responses, we asked several software engineering faculty members to complete the questionnaire. For both the hearing and Deaf/HoH students we surveyed, we also sought a wide, and diverse range of students. The students ranged from freshmen to others who were ready to graduate, and some had profound hearing loss while others were able to hear through the use of hearing aids or cochlear implants. A~\emph{cochlear implant} is a ``is a small, complex electronic device that can help to provide a sense of sound to a person who is profoundly deaf or severely hard-of-hearing. The implant consists of an external portion that sits behind the ear and a second portion that is surgically placed under the skin.'' The device circumvents the impaired hair cells in the inner year and uses electrical impulses to directly stimulate the auditory nerve~\cite{Zdenek:2007:FEV:1297144.1297198}.


