\subsection{Analysis}

Most faculty felt that the resources available to them to communicate their material to Deaf/HoH students were adequate enough for them to understand the material well enough to pass the course. This is interesting because most Deaf/HoH students reported that they felt the teacher's materials were unclear and very vague. Some students felt that the information itself was extremely vague and subsequently was interpreted as vague. This is a large roadblock in the learning environment, as many Deaf/HoH students want to succeed in academics.

